27. Overview of the entity’s material responsible business conduct issues: 
1. Material issue identified (Product Quality and Safety), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Negative: Product recalls and safety failures are costly and can severely impact customer trust and company reputation;
2. Material issue identified (Water Stewardship), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Negative:Poor water management can disrupt operations and lead to additional costs for water procurement and regulatory compliance.;
3. Material issue identified (Corporate Governance), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Negative: Inadequate governance can lead to regulatory fines, erode investor trust, and negatively impact market value.;
4. Material issue identified (Emissions Management), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Positive: With energy saving initiatives and efforts to mitigate, manage and minimise the emissions are expected to have positive financial and environmental implications.;
5. Material issue identified (Energy Management), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Positive: Effective energy management reduces costs and enhances the company's sustainability profile, attracting eco-conscious investors and customers.;
6. Material issue identified (Sustainable Strategy for Climate Resilience), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Positive: Proactive climate adaptation measures can lead to operational efficiencies, open new markets, and boost brand loyalty, positively affecting the bottom line.;
7. Material issue identified (Business Ethics and Compliance), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Negative: Failure to adhere to the code of conduct will have a negative reputational impact on employees and stakeholders.;
8. Material issue identified (Innovation and Digitalization), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Positive: Investments in digitalization typically yield high returns through improved market positioning and customer satisfaction.;
9. Material issue identified (Waste management & Circular Economy), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Positive: Managing waste at each stage of the manufacturing process directly impacts achieving resource efficiency and compliance with all applicable regulations, leading to positive financial impacts.;
10. Material issue identified (Ethical Procurement), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Negative: Ethical lapses could result in regulatory fines and loss of business credibility, adversely impacting financial performance.;
11. Material issue identified (Sustainable Supply Chain), Financial implications of the risk or opportunity (Indicate positive or negative implications): Negative: Disruptions or non-compliance in the supply chain can lead to increased costs and damage to the brand's reputation.

